<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4113] cqlsh does not work with piping</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4113</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I run cqlsh under ant like this&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;target name=&quot;create-test-db&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;exec executable=&quot;../dsc-cassandra-1.0.8/bin/cqlsh&quot; input=&quot;./resource/test/test.cql&quot;&amp;gt;  &lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;/exec&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/target&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I got: &lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Traceback (most recent call last):&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;   File &quot;../dsc-cassandra-1.0.8/bin/cqlsh&quot;, line 1891, in &amp;lt;module&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     main(*read_options(sys.argv&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1:&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, os.environ))&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;   File &quot;../dsc-cassandra-1.0.8/bin/cqlsh&quot;, line 1863, in main&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     completekey=options.completekey)&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;   File &quot;../dsc-cassandra-1.0.8/bin/cqlsh&quot;, line 384, in _&lt;em&gt;init&lt;/em&gt;_&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     self.output_codec = codecs.lookup(encoding)&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; TypeError: must be string, not None&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Result: 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest replacement of:&lt;br/&gt;
        if encoding is None:&lt;br/&gt;
            encoding = sys.stdout.encoding&lt;br/&gt;
to: &lt;br/&gt;
       if encoding is None:&lt;br/&gt;
           encoding=locale.getpreferredencoding()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
